newsitem.title: INDONESIA: Indonesia palm olein stable in late trading.
newsitem.headline: Indonesia palm olein stable in late trading.

text.p: Indonesian palm olein prices were stable in late trading on Tuesday as players stayed on the sidelines after early rises, traders said.

"Prices remain stable in late trading as many traders are taking a wait-and-see attitude following rises this morning," one Jakarta trader said, adding the earlier rises were buoyed by overnight rises in Malaysia.
They said olein was quoted at 1,435-40 rupiah/kg in Jakarta. They said offers were also heard at five rupiah above and below the range.

Data from Belawan Port showed that the MT Cakra-I will leave the North Sumatran port on Tuesday for Tanjung Priok, Jakarta, with 2,000 tonnes of olein. The MT Pan Oil 7 will arrive at the port on Wednesday with 3,600 tonnes of crude palm oil.
The MT Mahkota will leave the port on Tuesday for Cirebon with 1,600 tonnes of olein.
